OL,3,C10-year-old saddling up to keep Tony
OL,4,CHopper's memory alive
OL,6,F"I enjoy it because I like pushing
OL,7,Fmyself harder than I've ever pushed
OL,8,Fmyself before and I enjoy it because
OL,9,Fwhenever I ride, I normally always
OL,10,Ffind myself laughing at the end."
OL,12,FTony died after being diagnosed with
OL,13,FMotor Neurone Disease in 2018.
OL,15,FThe money raised by the riders will go
OL,16,Fto the MND association and Carlisle's
OL,17,FEden Valley Hospice and his family say
OL,18,Fthey hope this challenge will help
OL,19,Fkeep his memory alive.
